				I don't know.  If the gm's set the events, why should they  not be responsible for handing out the loot?  I have seen events where a person has validly won a roll but the raid leader refuses to give said person the loot because the raid leader doesn't think they should have it.  If a GM was the one dealing with the loot, said situation would not happen.   I personally think that as it is a GM event the GM should handle the playout and the loot distribution.
				
